    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the rice and pork have 15 min left, trim, then chop your<strong> green beans</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, the<strong> remaining dried oregano</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the beans to form a tightly sealed parcel[s] and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the beans are tender – these are your <strong>herby beans</strong></p>",
